						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Oziphantom wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">When I said more colours I meant &quot;more colours on screen&quot; something like Mayhem in Monsterland is known to have 20 colours on screen at once thanks to various blending tricks.</div><br />The NES can show 25 colors per screen without tricks.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">which means we can scroll without artifacts</div><br />The NES can scroll without artifacts too. Check out Jurassic Park, Felix the Cat, Alfred Chicken or Super Cars for various different ways in which it can be done. It's not the console's fault if Nintendo got &quot;lazy&quot; with its flagship title SMB3.</div>

