					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Filters 1, 2, and 3 are just nothing more than one of three fixed lowpass filters applied to filter 0.<br /><br />It's really only useful for fidelity when you can switch from block to block: if you use a constant setting you're instead just saying that you want that lowpass filtering.<br /><br />Actually, that's probably a good model for which filter to choose. The lower the pitches the softsynth is mixing, the stronger the lowpass filtering.</div><br /><br />If you have a 64 sample loop, it could happen where one part of the loop is busier than the other.</div>

